{"word":"ἀνιάω","slug":"ἀνιάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνιάω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἀνία'><el>ἀνία</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ῑ</el> in <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b> and <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <el>ι</el> or <el>ῑ</el> in other Poets.\n<p/>Like <el>ἀνιάζω</el>, <i>to grieve, distress</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> dupl. <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <el>ὁ δρῶν σ' ἀνιᾶι τὰς φρένας</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be grieved, distressed</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; with <a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>, <el>τοῦτ' ἀνιῶμαι</el> <i>I am vexed at</i> this, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; aor1 <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> as <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a>, <i>a sorrowful</i> man, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/>"}]}